# Cursor Rules — DiggAI Anamnese Platform

## Identity
This is DiggAI Anamnese Platform (Service 4 of 4-service DiggAI system).
Stack: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Express 5 + Prisma 6 + PostgreSQL 16.
Work EXCLUSIVELY in `anamnese-app/`. Do NOT touch sibling folders.

---

## NO-REDUNDANCY PROTOCOL — MANDATORY

Goldene Regel: Alles darf nur einmal gemacht werden. No duplicate work across sessions or agents.

Before creating any file, feature, route, service, or component, run from repo root (Anamnese-kimi/):

```powershell
# Step 1: Precheck
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/once-guard.ps1 precheck -Task "<task-key>"
# Exit 0 = free to proceed
# Exit 2 = BLOCKED — another agent has claimed this task
# Exit 3 = BLOCKED — task already completed, artifacts exist
# Exit 4 = WARNING — target artifact already exists on disk

# Step 2: Claim before starting
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/once-guard.ps1 claim -Task "<task-key>" -Agent "cursor" -SessionId "<YYYY-MM-DD-topic>"

# Step 3: Read shared knowledge
# shared/knowledge/knowledge-share.md  — past decisions, lessons learned, artifacts
# shared/knowledge/task-registry.json  — all tasks (in_progress / completed)

# Step 4: Do the work.

# Step 5: Mark complete with artifacts
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/once-guard.ps1 complete -Task "<task-key>" -Agent "cursor" -Artifacts @("server/routes/example.ts") -Notes "Brief summary"
```

If a file already exists on disk: READ IT FIRST. Extend, don't replace.
Policy doc: `../SESSIONS_ONCE_POLICY.md`

---

## Architecture

- Frontend: `src/` — React 19, Zustand 5, TanStack Query 5, React Router 7
- Backend: `server/` — Express 5, Prisma 6, Socket.IO 4, JWT, AES-256-GCM
- DB schema: `prisma/schema.prisma`
- All API hooks: `src/hooks/useApi.ts` (1500+ lines — read before touching)
- Medical questions: `src/data/questions.ts` (1246 lines — IDs are canonical, never renumber)

---

## Security Rules (Non-Negotiable)

- NEVER log patient names, emails, diagnoses — use IDs only
- ALWAYS use `server/services/encryption.ts` (AES-256-GCM) for PII fields
- ALWAYS use HttpOnly cookies for JWT — never localStorage
- NEVER bypass `server/middleware/auth.ts` on patient-data routes
- NEVER hardcode secrets — use `.env`

---

## Code Conventions

- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`
- Functional React components only, hooks for state
- All user-facing strings via `useTranslation()` — no hardcoded German text
- Tailwind utility classes only — no CSS modules
- TanStack React Query for all API calls
- Prisma ORM only — no raw SQL
- All new API endpoints: auth middleware + Zod validation + audit log

---

## i18n (10 languages)

ALL new UI strings need keys in ALL 10 locale files:
`public/locales/{de,en,tr,ar,uk,es,fa,it,fr,pl}/translation.json`
German (de) is source of truth. Run `node scripts/generate-i18n.ts` to check.

---

## Forbidden

- No patient data in URLs or query strings
- No `console.log` of sensitive data in production
- No raw SQL — Prisma only
- No new triage logic outside `server/engine/TriageEngine.ts`
- No TriageEngine changes without clinical sign-off (Dr. Klapproth / Dr. Al-Shdaifat)
- No git push --force to main
- No skipping Prisma migrations after schema changes

---

## Brainstorm Flow

New feature ideas go through the 4-agent brainstorm before implementation:
```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ../scripts/agent-brainstorm.ps1 init -Topic "<topic>"
```
See `../AGENT_BRAINSTORM_FLOW.md` for full protocol.


---

## Definition of Done — Memory Discipline (REQUIRED for every prompt)

A prompt with an observable outcome (commit, file change, PR, deployment, decision) is NOT done until you append a 5-line run-log entry at:

```
Ananmese/diggai-anamnese-master/memory/runs/YYYY-MM-DD_<agent>_<model>-<run>.md
```

**Naming rules.**
- `<agent>` = lowercase short name. Established: `claude-code`, `copilot`, `codex`, `kimi`, `gemini`, `cursor`. Pick one and reuse it.
- `<model>` = short tag. Examples: `opus-4-7`, `sonnet-4-6`, `gpt-5`, `gemini-2-5`, `kimi-k2`.
- `<run>` = monotonic counter for that (agent, model) pair on this calendar day. `01`, `02`, …

**Format (matches existing Kimi pattern in `memory/runs/`):**

```markdown
YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM+02:00 | Lauf <agent>-<run> | <one-line topic>
---
- Aktion: <what you did, concrete>
- Blocker: <what tripped you, or "—">
- Fix: <how you got past it, or "—">
- Ergebnis: <observable outcome — commit hash, PR #, file path>
- Out: <verified state — "tests green", "PR #N open", "blocked on F1-F8", …>
```

**Why this is non-negotiable.** Agents lose context between sessions but the run-log persists. The next agent reads the last 3 entries and knows what was tried, what works on this machine, and what is still open. Without this log the engineering-harness advantage is forfeited and the next agent re-discovers the same footguns.

See workspace-root [`AGENT_PREFLIGHT_PROTOCOL.md`](../AGENT_PREFLIGHT_PROTOCOL.md) §10 for the full preflight context (boot checklist, tool decision tree, machine footguns, append-log).
